-- Deutsche Bank Appoints Smith Head of Corporate Commodity Sales for Asia
-- Christian Schmollinger
-- 2010-07-05T01:22:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/deutsche-bank-appoints-smith-head-of-corporate-commodity-sales-for-asia.html

          
          
             Deutsche Bank AG  appointed  Stuart Smith , an ex-director of JPMorgan Chase & Co., to head corporate
commodity sales for Asia outside Japan, the company said.  
 Smith will be based in Singapore and report to  Brian Cumming , the global head of oil sales, according to the
statement released today. At JPMorgan, Smith covered sales in
Australasia and Southeast Asia and before that he ran the
liquefied natural gas trading section at Goldman Sachs Group Inc.
in London.  
 Smith received a doctorate in petroleum geology and
geophysics from the University of Adelaide.  
